<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION SHIFT LINKAGE - INSTALL - BRAKE
        CONTROL ROD ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BRAKE CONTROL ROD ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Transmission shift lever must be in "P-B" position and the hand control valve TW-12 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 1, Figure 4</hotlnk>) actuating ball engaged in the slot in the TW-12
                    valve actuating cam.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1303104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1303104" filename="../figg13/G1303104.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Shift Lever Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HAND CONTROL VALVE (TW12)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEX NUT, JAM</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BRAKE CONTROL ROD SWIVEL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BRAKE CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                <callout1>5. TRANSMISSION CABLE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. TRANSMISSION SHIFT LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>7. CONTROL LEVER PIVOT PIN, WASHERS, AND COTTER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>8. SPECIAL LOCK OR FLAT WASHERS (HARDENED)</callout1>
                <callout1>9. COTTER PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>10. CABLE BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach brake control rod swivel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 3, Figure 4</hotlnk>) to brake control rod (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach brake control rod swivel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 3, Figure 4</hotlnk>) to hand control valve cam using hardened special
                lock or flat washers and cotter pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust the brake control rod (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>) by rotating the swivel to align with the hole in
                the upper transmission shift lever.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Ensure rod offset faces inboard.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach brake control rod (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 4, Figure 4</hotlnk>) to transmission shift lever (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 6, Figure 4</hotlnk>) using control lever pivot pin, washers, and cotter
                pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303104">Item 7, Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
